I"J<p>Compassion is the foundation for empathy, love and compromise in relationships.</p>

<p>Compassion is an attitude and belief in equality and each persons right to be valued and understood.</p>

<p>When you do not judge or criticise the behaviour of another person but take time to understand and work through problems together, you show the other person that you do not see problems in the relationship as indications of their worth.</p>

<p>Instead, you see working through problems  as an opportunity for growth that can provide deeper levels of understanding and connection.</p>

